    <h1>About MP Luminaries</h1>
    <p class="dek">Two stories every evening about the people doing right by Madhya Pradesh.</p>
  </header>
  <div class="article-body">
    <p>Open a newspaper and you will mostly read about what broke, who failed, and why things are getting worse. MP Luminaries exists to cover the other half of the story. Every day at 8&nbsp;PM IST we publish two new profiles of people whose work deserves to be better known — chief ministers and village sarpanchs, IAS officers and constables, Olympians, actors, scientists and founders. Our focus is Madhya Pradesh, with an occasional national figure whose work touches us all.</p>
    <h2>How we work</h2>
    <p>Every story on this site is grounded in published, verifiable reporting. We do not invent achievements, and each article ends with links to the original reporting it draws on. If we get something wrong, write to <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a> and we will correct it.</p>
    <h2>About our artwork</h2>
    <p>The portraits on MP Luminaries are original editorial illustrations created with the assistance of AI tools, in a deliberately artistic style. They are not photographs, and they are not copies of any existing photograph. We do this so we can celebrate people without infringing on photographers' work — and we label every image so you always know what you are looking at.</p>
    <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
    <p>MP Luminaries celebrates good work wherever it happens, across parties, departments and industries. Featuring a person here is recognition of a specific, reported accomplishment — not a political endorsement.</p>
  </div>
</article>
